# Cross-build and static smbd environment.
# Samba 4.24 marks some generated tools as hostcc but still lets waf inherit
# target compiler/linker settings. Keep those host tools on the VM compiler,
# while applying static link flags only to the smbd binary we deploy.
0001-waf-cross-static-env.patch|waf hostcc and static smbd environment

# NetBSD runtime compatibility.
# NetBSD4 lacks newer libc symbols, and the runtime kernels are older than the
# SDKs used to compile these binaries. Keep normal file serving on path-based
# VFS fallbacks instead of relying on runtime *at/openat2/fdopendir support.
0002-netbsd4-libreplace-compat.patch|NetBSD4 libc compatibility shims
0003-netbsd-vfs-runtime-fallbacks.patch|Time Capsule VFS runtime syscall fallbacks
# NetBSD4 can lose Samba's cached is_directory flag even when stat still says
# the handle is a directory; recover before rejecting SMB2 QUERY_DIRECTORY.
0004-netbsd4-query-directory-stat-fallback.patch|NetBSD4 SMB2 directory stat fallback

# Single-binary smbd behavior.
# Finder and smbclient enumerate shares through IPC$ srvsvc. Embed that one
# pipe in smbd because the Time Capsule RAM-disk deployment cannot rely on
# external DCE/RPC helper binaries living on an Apple-managed HFS disk.
0005-smbd-embedded-srvsvc.patch|embedded srvsvc named pipe support
# smbd -V exits through shared option parsing before server.c can clean up.
0006-smbd-version-no-dangling-frame.patch|clean smbd version exit
# Reopened TDB handles should not leak into any helper exec path.
0007-tdb-cloexec-compat.patch|TDB close-on-exec compatibility

# No-pthread appliance runtime behavior.
# Time Capsule kernels do not support the pthread behavior Samba 4.24 expects.
# Host long-lived notifyd/cleanupd/scavenger work in the smbd parent event loop
# and avoid helper forks that hit raw abort paths on these targets.
0008-no-pthread-smbd-daemons-in-parent.patch|host smbd helper services in the parent event loop
# Avoid pthreadpool-backed messaging paths while preserving Samba's watched
# SMBX database wrappers; client/session callers still require watched records.
0009-no-pthread-messaging-and-db-fallbacks.patch|no-pthread messaging fallbacks
# The static appliance build does not launch winbindd; keep local mappings and
# skip libwbclient lookups for the remaining Windows SIDs during startup.
0010-no-pthread-local-sid-to-unixids.patch|local SID mapping without winbindd
# smbXsrv_version_global_init retains global DB state after returning; parent
# it to an explicit named context instead of the process-global talloc stack.
0011-no-pthread-smbxsrv-version-global-parent.patch|explicit parent for retained SMBX version state
# tevent's pooled request, call-depth, and threaded-context paths assume
# pthread/TLS behavior that the appliance build removes after configure.
0012-no-pthread-tevent-fallbacks.patch|tevent fallbacks for no-pthread builds
# Configure may see pthread/TLS on the VM before the target cache is scrubbed;
# make the final no-pthread build use process-global storage for __thread uses.
0013-no-pthread-tls-fallbacks.patch|no-pthread TLS configure and __thread fallback
# The no-pthread talloc stack is process-global, so forked smbd children inherit
# parent event-loop stack tracking. Drop inherited tracking after fork and
# disarm normal-exit diagnostics once smbd has completed clean shutdown.
0022-no-pthread-talloc-stack-fork-exit-cleanup.patch|no-pthread talloc stack fork and exit cleanup

# Static build compile fixes.
# This reduced nonshared build can expose duplicate typedefs through multiple
# include paths; guard the typedefs instead of relying on fragile include order.
0014-typedef-guards.patch|duplicate typedef guards
# NetBSD4 lacks posix_spawn, but local named pipe and print queue code still
# compile into the static smbd target even though printing is not enabled.
0015-netbsd-posix-spawn-fallbacks.patch|NetBSD posix_spawn fallbacks
# Samba's bundled popt fallback collides with libc glob_pattern_p in the static
# NetBSD lanes; rename the bundled private symbol.
0016-popt-glob-symbol-rename.patch|bundled popt glob symbol rename
# Time Capsule lock databases live on a tiny RAM disk. Let smb.conf force
# volatile dbwrap TDB deletes onto the global freelist instead of retaining
# thousands of per-hash-chain dead records after Time Machine closes files.
0017-dbwrap-tdb-max-dead-config.patch|configurable dbwrap TDB max-dead records
# macOS and Time Machine probe stream/ACL xattrs on untouched files. When
# xattr_tdb backs that metadata, a missing row must behave like an empty xattr
# set, not EINVAL. This is a real macOS interoperability fix, not a NetBSD shim,
# and likely applies to future Samba versions that still use xattr_tdb here.
0018-xattr-tdb-missing-row-empty-xattrs.patch|xattr_tdb missing rows behave like empty xattrs
# macOS/iOS Photos writes many assetsd metadata streams. Once xattr_tdb's
# stream-name list exceeds Samba's initial 1024-byte listxattr buffer, return
# the normal -1/ERANGE retry signal instead of a positive required length that
# callers mistake for bytes written into the too-small buffer.
0027-xattr-tdb-listattr-erange.patch|xattr_tdb retries oversized xattr name lists
# Time Machine durable handles on HFS sparsebundle bands should not treat
# allocation-block count drift as file identity loss after reconnect.
0019-time-machine-durable-st-ex-blocks.patch|allow durable reconnect across HFS allocation-block drift
# Time Machine can retry SMB2 durable opens before the old smbd has marked the
# open disconnected; retry once outside the open-global TDB lock instead of
# reporting the durable handle as permanently missing.
0024-time-machine-durable-open-live-retry.patch|retry transient live durable-open reconnect races
# Time Capsule kernels can hang in native NetBSD getifaddrs(); force Samba's
# interface enumeration through libreplace's ioctl-based fallback.
0020-netbsd-getifaddrs-fallback.patch|force ioctl-based interface enumeration on NetBSD
# macOS Finder and Time Machine stat AFP_AfpInfo streams during ordinary copy
# and sparsebundle work. Samba 4.24's fruit fstatat path accidentally
# dereferences the yet-to-be-created no-stream filename copy, crashing the smbd
# client process. Keep this until upstream fixes vfs_fruit.
0021-vfs-fruit-fstatat-meta-stream-name.patch|fix vfs_fruit AFP_AfpInfo fstatat NULL filename crash
# Time Capsule payload logs live on Apple-managed HFS, where root-created
# directories can report owner 4294967295 and fail Samba's strict corepath
# setup. Relax only the appliance core directory creation so panics produce
# disk-backed cores under logs/cores/smbd.
0023-time-capsule-corepath-hfs-owner.patch|allow HFS-backed smbd corepath setup
# Time Capsule HFS can report served file owner/group as 4294967295. Normalize
# only that HFS sentinel at Samba's stat_ex boundary so ACL, stream, and
# security descriptor paths see the forced root/wheel appliance identity.
0025-time-capsule-hfs-stat-owner.patch|normalize HFS unknown owner in stat metadata
# Samba's default streaminfo layer refreshes stat before appending ::$DATA.
# The Time Capsule pathref fallback can fail that refresh even when the open
# path has already cached valid stat metadata; keep stream enumeration alive
# for macOS delete/share checks without hiding failures on uncached paths.
0026-time-capsule-fstreaminfo-cached-stat.patch|use cached stat for default streaminfo fallback
# macOS Time Machine sends FSCTL_SRV_REQUEST_RESUME_KEY inside a compounded
# request while probing backup-disk capabilities. The default VFS can complete
# that resume-key request synchronously, but wrapper layers must propagate the
# completed state before the SMB2 compound guard treats it as illegal async IOCTL
# work and returns NT_STATUS_INTERNAL_ERROR.
0028-time-machine-resume-key-sync-completion.patch|propagate synchronous resume-key IOCTL completion
